snippet.description:
Bertie Gregory heads to the Azores, a remote island chain in the Atlantic Ocean. Surrounded by Europe‚Äôs largest marine protected area, these waters are a vital stop for migrating predators, drawn here by rich feeding grounds. It‚Äôs the perfect time for Bertie to capture a rare natural spectacle‚Äîwhen elusive predators unite to hunt dense shoals of fish called bait balls. But with unpredictable storms, filming won‚Äôt be easy. During his journey, Bertie also explores the region‚Äôs dark history of marine exploitation. By meeting an ex-whaler turned whale spotter, he discovers how the end of whaling transformed the Azores into a sanctuary, allowing marine life to return and delicate food chains to thrive.

it.description:
Bertie Gregory si dirige alle Azzorre, un remoto arcipelago nell'Oceano Atlantico. Circondate dalla pi√π grande area marina protetta d'Europa, queste acque rappresentano una tappa fondamentale per i predatori migratori, attratti dalle ricche zone di alimentazione. √à il momento perfetto per Bertie per immortalare un raro spettacolo naturale: quando predatori sfuggenti si uniscono per cacciare densi banchi di pesci chiamati "bait balls". Ma con tempeste imprevedibili, le riprese non saranno facili. Durante il suo viaggio, Bertie esplora anche la cupa storia di sfruttamento marino della regione. Incontrando un ex baleniere diventato osservatore di balene, scopre come la fine della caccia alle balene abbia trasformato le Azzorre in un santuario, consentendo alla vita marina di tornare e alle delicate catene alimentari di prosperare.

nl-NL.title: Dolfijnen van dichtbij met Bertie Gregory | Offici√´le trailer | National Geographic
nl-NL.description:
Bertie Gregory reist af naar de Azoren, een afgelegen eilandengroep in de Atlantische Oceaan. Omringd door Europa's grootste beschermde zeegebied, vormen deze wateren een onmisbare halteplaats voor migrerende roofdieren, die hierheen worden gelokt door rijke voedselgebieden. Het is het perfecte moment voor Bertie om een zeldzaam natuurspektakel vast te leggen: wanneer ongrijpbare roofdieren zich verenigen om te jagen op dichte scholen vis, zogenaamde aasballen. Maar met onvoorspelbare stormen zal filmen niet eenvoudig zijn. Tijdens zijn reis verkent Bertie ook de duistere geschiedenis van mariene exploitatie in de regio. Door een ontmoeting met een voormalig walvisvaarder die walvisspotter werd, ontdekt hij hoe het einde van de walvisvaart de Azoren heeft veranderd in een toevluchtsoord, waardoor het zeeleven kon terugkeren en kwetsbare voedselketens konden floreren.

id.title: Lumba-lumba dari Dekat bersama Bertie Gregory | Trailer Resmi | National Geographic
id.description:
Bertie Gregory menuju Azores, gugusan pulau terpencil di Samudra Atlantik. Dikelilingi oleh kawasan lindung laut terbesar di Eropa, perairan ini merupakan persinggahan penting bagi predator yang bermigrasi, yang tertarik ke sini oleh tempat makan yang kaya. Inilah saat yang tepat bagi Bertie untuk mengabadikan pemandangan alam yang langka‚Äîketika predator yang sulit ditangkap bersatu untuk memburu gerombolan ikan padat yang disebut bola umpan. Namun, dengan badai yang tak terduga, pengambilan gambar menjadi tidak mudah. Selama perjalanannya, Bertie juga menjelajahi sejarah kelam eksploitasi laut di wilayah tersebut. Dengan bertemu seorang mantan pemburu paus yang kini menjadi pengamat paus, ia menemukan bagaimana berakhirnya perburuan paus mengubah Azores menjadi suaka margasatwa, yang memungkinkan kehidupan laut pulih dan rantai makanan yang rapuh berkembang.

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger," starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2", the sixth film in the YRF Spy Universe, starring Hrithik Roshan, NTR and Kiara Advani, directed by Ayan Mukerji, released on 14 August 2025. "Alpha", the seventh film in the franchise and Hindi cinema‚Äôs first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, will release on 25 December 2025.

snippet.title: Bipul Chettri - Eh Saathi (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
'Eh Saathi' is the first release from the forthcoming album, 'Pravah'. As the title suggests, it's an ode to childhood friendships that transcends time. Almost written like a conversation piece put to music, the song embodies the notion of friendship that is something to nurture and celebrate, that you never take them for granted and its enduring nature of emphasizing loyalty, love, and the shared journey of life.

Please switch on the CC button for English subtitles.

MUSIC
Bipul Chettri - Vocals, Guitars, Backing Vocals 
Pranai Gurung - Guitars
Rahul Rai - Bass
Rythem Bansal - Keys/Organ
Shantanu Sudarshan - Drums/Percussions 
Sumimardor Diengdoh, Bhushan Man Amatya, Prashansa Pandey Amatya - Backing Vocals 

Written and arranged by Bipul Chettri.
Recorded at Baa Baa Black Sheep Studios, Plug ‚ÄòN‚Äô Play Studios & Project Studio Productions.
Recording Engineers - Jonty Indra, Anindo Bose, Binaya Man Amatya 
Mixed & Mastered by Binaya Man Amatya
Album Cover Design - Manohar Rai
Album Cover Photography - Praveen Chettri
Producer - Bipul Chettri
Executive Producer - Sonam Tashi

Director of Photography: Vashistha Pradhan 
Chief Assistant Director: Sujan Lamjel

Don‚Äôt know where you sleep lately

It‚Äôs bittersweet
Can we be friends at least

snippet.title: Primitive War - Official Spot | In Theaters August 21
snippet.description:
This ain‚Äôt no walk in the park. Watch the full Primitive War trailer now.

'PRIMITIVE WAR' coming to theatres across the USA and Australia AUGUST 21 2025 proudly presented by Fathom Entertainment and Rialto Distribution. Followed by release worldwide.

From director Luke Sparke comes PRIMITIVE WAR based on the popular novel 'The Primitive War' by Ethan Pettus.
Vietnam. 1968. A recon unit known as Vulture Squad is sent to an isolated jungle valley to uncover the fate of a missing Green Beret platoon. They soon discover they are not alone.
Sparke Films in association with Let it be Entertainment and producers Carly Sparke, Carmel Imrie, Luke Sparke, Geoff Imrie and Alex Becconsall presents PRIMITIVE WAR. An action-packed war film that pits battle hardened soldiers against the greatest predators that ever walked the earth.

Presented by Primitive War

üé∂ Mutu Mai Basechha (Female Version Cover) üé∂

Originally performed by Brijesh Shrestha/Samikshya Adhikari, this is my heartfelt female interpretation of the beautiful song Mutu Mai Basechha. I've added some extra verses to express a different emotional perspective‚Äîone that reflects a softer, more intimate side of the story.

‚ú® This version is not just a cover‚Äîit's a reimagined expression of love, pain, and longing from a female voice. I hope you connect with this rendition just as deeply as I did while creating it.

‚ú® Achyutam Keshavam ‚Äì A Devotional Krishna Bhajan ‚ú®
 "Achyutam Keshavam" is a timeless and soul-soothing bhajan dedicated to Lord Krishna, praising their divine names, virtues, and forms. The bhajan beautifully recites various names of the Lord - Achyuta, Keshava, Narayana, and more - each carrying deep spiritual meaning.
Singing this bhajan is believed to purify the heart, remove sorrows, and bring the blessings of the Supreme Lord. It reminds devotees to surrender completely to God, trusting His eternal protection and grace.


üå∏ Chant ‚ÄúAchyutam Keshavam‚Äù with devotion and invite divine bliss into your life.

‚ú® Achyutam Keshavam ‚Äì A Devotional Krishna Bhajan ‚ú®
 "Achyutam Keshavam" is a timeless and soul-soothing bhajan dedicated to Lord Krishna, praising their divine names, virtues, and forms. The bhajan beautifully recites various names of the Lord - Achyuta, Keshava, Narayana, and more - each carrying deep spiritual meaning.
Singing this bhajan is believed to purify the heart, remove sorrows, and bring the blessings of the Supreme Lord. It reminds devotees to surrender completely to God, trusting His eternal protection and grace.


üå∏ Chant ‚ÄúAchyutam Keshavam‚Äù with devotion and invite divine bliss into your life.
